OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F446A1772718049
OL,3,CMcNally murder trial told how accused
OL,4,Cgrieved with family in days after
OL,5,Ckilling
OL,7,FThe 32-year-old was found strangled,
OL,8,Fstabbed and beaten to death in her
OL,9,FSilverwood Green home in Lurgan in
OL,10,FDecember 2022.
OL,12,FHer boyfriend and father to her unborn
OL,13,Fchild Stephen McCullagh is accused of
OL,14,Fher murder. He denies the charge.
OL,16,FThe jury of six men and six women
OL,17,Fheard how the 36-year-old of Woodland
OL,18,FGardens in Lisburn attended the wake
OL,19,Fat her parent's house on Christmas Day
OL,20,F2022 and was given time alone with the
OL,21,Fcoffin for around 20 minutes.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G2/10
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,447,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44603
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F446A1772718049
OL,3,CMcNally murder trial told how accused
OL,4,Cgrieved with family in days after
OL,5,Ckilling
OL,7,FNatalie's father Noel McNally told the
OL,8,Fjury they welcomed him into their
OL,9,Fhouse and treated him like a grieving
OL,10,Fpartner and father-to-be because the
OL,11,Fpolice had told them he was no longer
OL,12,Fa suspect and, as far as they were
OL,13,Fconcerned, he had nothing to do with
OL,14,FNatalie's death.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G3/10
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,447,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44604
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F446A1772718049
OL,3,CMcNally murder trial told how accused
OL,4,Cgrieved with family in days after
OL,5,Ckilling
OL,7,FNatalie's mother Bernadette McNally
OL,8,Ftold the court she was "devastated and
OL,9,Fworried" for McCullagh. She described
OL,10,Fhow he was left alone with the coffin
OL,11,Fbecause, out of generosity, the family
OL,12,Fthought he would want some time with
OL,13,FNatalie.
OL,15,FThe court heard how the family hugged
OL,16,Fand consoled him. Bernadette McNally
OL,17,Fbroke down and became very upset as
OL,18,Fshe described her daughter's murder as
OL,19,F"devastating".
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G4/10
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,447,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44605
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F446A1772718049
OL,3,CMcNally murder trial told how accused
OL,4,Cgrieved with family in days after
OL,5,Ckilling
OL,7,FThe defence asked Noel McNally did he
OL,8,Fhave any inkling of a suggestion if
OL,9,Fthere had been a fallout between
OL,10,FNatalie and the defendant. He replied
OL,11,F"absolutely not" and described how the
OL,12,Flast time he had seen his daughter
OL,13,Falive was the day of her murder and
OL,14,Fshe was in good form.
OL,16,FThe court was told in the days after
OL,17,FNatalie's murder McCullagh called to
OL,18,Fthe parents house a number of times
OL,19,Fbut didn't attend the funeral because
OL,20,Fit would be too much.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G5/10
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
