OL,3,CMcNally murder trial told how accused
OL,4,Cgrieved with family in days after
OL,5,Ckilling
OL,7,FOne of Natalie's brothers explained he
OL,8,Fwould text McCullagh daily after his
OL,9,Fsister's death and how he then went to
OL,10,FNatalie's grave with him.
OL,12,FDeclan McNally said Stephen McCullagh
OL,13,Fseemed "distraught" when they got
OL,14,Fthere and said 'how could someone do
OL,15,Fthis to her?'"
OL,17,FHe also told of how he found Natalie
OL,18,Fface down in a dog bowl saying
OL,19,F"someone had left her like an animal".
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G6/10
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,447,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44607
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F446A1772718049
OL,3,CMcNally murder trial told how accused
OL,4,Cgrieved with family in days after
OL,5,Ckilling
OL,7,FDeclan described how he was shocked by
OL,8,Fwhat McCullagh was telling him and
OL,9,Fthat McCullagh told him he believed
OL,10,FNatalie's ex had gone to her house and
OL,11,Ffound out she was pregnant and in a
OL,12,Frage killed her.
OL,14,FDuring cross examination, the defence
OL,15,Fasked some of the family members about
OL,16,Fwhat they knew about her ex. They said
OL,17,Fthey were unaware of any suggestions
OL,18,Fthat her ex-boyfriend had been abusive.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G7/10
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
